rComments: Oh what can I say more about my girl Jenny; the uttermost worst professor I have ever had at UofT. I'm a 4.0 student, with 20 offers to law schools across Canada and the United States and even I had such a tough time with this person. Completely not compassionate, hard grader, and lacks basic communicative skills. For good or bad, don't take this

She is by far the most horrible and uncompassionate person I have ever met. She is so rude and has the worst feedback. For someone who teaches compassion and supposedly has a PhD in education she doesn't anything about treating students. She will never make time to see you after class and her responses to emails are violent. DO NOT TAKE HER CLASS!

Disorganized. Errors on syllabus/ assignments, changes dates. Reads slides off laptop, doesn't post before class so she can correct errors she finds during class (umm, edit much?!) Gets annoyed & wants a reason if you miss a couple classes (it's an elective!). Least compassionate instructor I've had at U of T, ironic given she teaches compassion.
Jennifer is an amazing person. Such a gentle soul who wants nothing but success for her students. I took away so much from this class and I am so grateful.

Unclear about the grading criteria, you won't get much guidance for the essays. Not very organized. Mostly reads of the lecture slides. Has tons of readings but will only include a few on the test.  Not the best at accommodating students with accessibility needs.
